<p>Dear Family, Friends, and Colleagues,</p>

<p>What is remarkable about most of the past week may be how unremarkable it
was: after a long storm (our 4th!) which stopped our work last Thursday
morning finally abated in the wee hours Saturday, we have been working
steadily on our measurement program, just as we usually do and expect to do
on these cruises. We are making fine progress, though are about 4.5 days
behind the expedition deadline timeline. Small problems pop up in the
equipment from time to time, and we have found some ways to improve a few
procedures - pretty much business as usual. (I'll get into our science
program in future letters.) The sameness of the work - we are either on
station or steaming between stations around the clock - is an oddly
comforting measure of progress. Of course, we very much enjoy the little
breaks nature provides...</p>

