 <p>Along with some clear periods during days has come
 some clear periods at night, and we have seen the
 Aurora Australis ("Southern Lights") a few times.
 Our PolarTREC teacher, Juan Botella, captured some
 excellent night photos from a moving ship (!). I
 have attached two, enhanced for light level only.
 Notice the stars of Orion's belt in one of them?</p>

